import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zipcodes_by_state = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(zipcodes_by_state.index, zipcodes_by_state.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['latitude'], bins=30, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['latitude'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['latitude'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['latitude'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['latitude'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude values?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_names = data['city'].value_counts().index.tolist()
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts().tolist()
    city_dict = dict(zip(city_names, city_counts))
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='white', 
                min_font_size = 10).generate_from_frequencies(city_dict)
    plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8), facecolor = None) 
    plt.imshow(wordcloud) 
    plt.axis("off") 
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 0) 
    plt.title('What is the most common city in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
